      "rationale": "N=11 production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled per device master record. Geometric measurements (CMM) confirm all critical dimensions within drawing tolerance. Samples distributed across two independent laboratories to assess inter-lab variability. Sample traceability documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two rod diameters and two screw offset configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (5.5 mm rod, 35 mm offset) due to resource constraints. While this configuration represents the most common clinical scenario, the absence of additional rod diameters and offset distances means the required level of 3 is not achieved. This gap is acknowledged and accepted at the medium model risk level with compensating analytical sensitivity studies."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test article parameters within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured geometry of each test construct used to individualize the corresponding FEA model. Material properties from same production lot as test articles. Fixture boundary conditions replicate F1717 test machine constraints. Equivalency confirmed through parameter-by-parameter comparison table documented in the validation report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percentage difference < 10% for each construct-model pair.",
      "rationale": "Validation metric E/uval computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement per ASME V&V 40 Section 5. Results: stiffness E/uval = 1.12, yield force E/uval = 0.94, force at 40 mm E/uval = 1.31. All three metrics below 1.96 threshold. Maximum percentage difference across all construct-model pairs was 7.8%, within the 10% acceptance bound."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
