      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly map to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are explicitly required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions and directly correspond to construct fatigue life prediction inputs. Stiffness governs load sharing with bone; yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm characterizes post-yield energy absorption. QoI relevance to the COU is high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
