    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted based on: (1) the tested configuration represents the predominant clinical use scenario; (2) analytical sensitivity studies demonstrate QoI insensitivity to rod diameter variation within the clinical range; and (3) the medium model risk level and medium decision consequence do not mandate full multi-configuration coverage. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a regulatory submission decision at medium assurance level.",
